    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>On February 12, 1964, by the time the clock struck 7:30 p.m. my best friend and I sat on the edges of our seats in Carnegie Hall and watched the second-ever-in-the U.S. concert given by the Beatles.  We were instantly transformed into the coolest kids in our high school.   I am telling you this so I have a little street cred when I say the only concert I ever walked out on &#8211; and it was within the first fifteen minutes &#8211; was a Fleetwood Mac concert at the Onmi in Atlanta a million years ago.  </p>
<p>So I&#39;m passing on the Stevie Nicks&#39; videos.</p>
<p>But not the scones.  As always, thanks, Molly.</p>
    </div>

