  <li id="comment-29220" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/13215328104522170640" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">olan</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/08/it-still-surprises-me/#comment-29220"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-09-01T05:09:16-04:00">Thursday, September 1, 2011 at 5:09 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I used to make those scones at Standard!  I recommend dusting the counter with flour and oats since the dough is very sticky and you get extra oat-y crunch.  The turbinado sugar garnish adds excellent crispiness and sweetness since the scone isn&#39;t very sweet.  Rolling the turbinado and oat garnish into the scones before cutting prevents them from falling off but don&#39;t over do it or it won&#39;t look rustic.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-29356" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/13215328104522170640" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">olan</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/08/it-still-surprises-me/#comment-29356"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-09-01T05:09:16-04:00">Thursday, September 1, 2011 at 5:09 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I used to make those scones at Standard!  I recommend dusting the counter with flour and oats since the dough is very sticky and you get extra oat-y crunch.  The turbinado sugar garnish adds excellent crispiness and sweetness since the scone isn&#39;t very sweet.  Rolling the turbinado and oat garnish into the scones before cutting prevents them from falling off but don&#39;t over do it or it won&#39;t look rustic.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-29221" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Pauline</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/08/it-still-surprises-me/#comment-29221"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-09-02T03:05:12-04:00">Friday, September 2, 2011 at 3:05 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just picked 34 cups of blackberries from the brambles taking over my front yard. I&#39;ll definitely try these out while using a few of my berries.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
