      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-29226" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/16883504723581554701" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">jessica.</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/08/it-still-surprises-me/#comment-29226"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-09-17T01:53:52-04:00">Saturday, September 17, 2011 at 1:53 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve made these a few times now, with different fruit each time (PEACHES, y&#39;all, do it), and I&#39;ve found this little tweak to the method really helps to cure that crushing-the-berries ailment:</p>
<p>Toss your fruit into the dry mixture to blend it well, and then pour the vanilla&#39;ed HnH over top (drizzle it around a bit). I let it sit for about two minutes, then come back and give it a quick 1-2-3 stir, and it&#39;s perfect!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-29362" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/16883504723581554701" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">jessica.</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/08/it-still-surprises-me/#comment-29362"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-09-17T01:53:52-04:00">Saturday, September 17, 2011 at 1:53 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve made these a few times now, with different fruit each time (PEACHES, y&#39;all, do it), and I&#39;ve found this little tweak to the method really helps to cure that crushing-the-berries ailment:</p>
<p>Toss your fruit into the dry mixture to blend it well, and then pour the vanilla&#39;ed HnH over top (drizzle it around a bit). I let it sit for about two minutes, then come back and give it a quick 1-2-3 stir, and it&#39;s perfect!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
